    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n(nightly) I manage my nvim configuration via nix and the `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nvim` path is a symlink to a readonly directory in the nix store. So, nvim can't create/update the lockfile.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt would be nice to be able to configure the location of vim.pack-lockfile. It could be an option like `vim.opt.packlockfile`. I would love to take a shot at implementing this if you're open to it.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
