            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There are plenty of ways to configure paths already (xdg, NVIM_APPNAME), I dont see a strong usecase for being able to configure this special one. I suppose you manage your config via home-manager. I intend to change its behavior (ok it has been 4 years) via https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager/pull/5964 ) which would solve this issue. If you use a full nix config, you are not supposed to use vim.pack anyway :)",
