            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> There are plenty of ways to configure paths already (xdg, NVIM_APPNAME)\n\nNot sure I understood what you mean here since it would still attempt to write to the directory that the config is in when nvim loads.\n\n> I suppose you manage your config via home-manager. I intend to change its behavior...\n\nThats great! But I don't know if neovim should rely on assumptions like that? Which is why I feel it is appropriate for the lockfile path to be configurable in neovim. Not that my personal preference matters here, but that was the reason I suggested this.",
